The paper deals with the computational complexity of computing the noncommutative determinant and its relation to other problems such as the noncommutative permanent and the commutative permanent. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the computational complexity (cs.CC) and data structures and algorithms (cs.DS) sub-categories. The paper also uses techniques related to algebraic geometry and linear algebra, which could place it in the computational geometry (cs.CG), logic in computer science (cs.LO), or scientific computing (cs.SC) sub-categories.
